Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.language.reflection.property

Class PropertySet

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.language.reflection.property.PropertySet
All Implemented Interfaces:
PropertyFilter
Direct Known Subclasses:
AllFields, AllMethods
public class PropertySet extends Object implements PropertyFilter
Base class for property filters. Supports Java Beans and KivaKit style accessor naming conventions with the enum PropertyNamingConvention and filtering of properties and fields with PropertyMemberSelector. The constructor takes a style and a set of explicit includes (nothing is included by default). Static fields and properties are never included. Any field or method tagged with ExcludeProperty will be excluded regardless of the inclusions specified.

Subclasses can utilize the following tests to implement filters that don't follow the pattern implemented by this base class.

Getters and Setters

  • isGetter(Method) - True if the method is a getter under the given naming convention
  • isSetter(Method) - True if the method is a setter under the given naming convention

Include Tests

  • isIncluded(Method) - True if the method is included under the given set of PropertyMemberSelectors
  • isIncluded(Field) - True if the field is included under the given set of PropertyMemberSelectors

KivaKit Annotation Tests

  • isIncludedByAnnotation(Method) - True if the method is annotated with IncludeProperty
  • isIncludedByAnnotation(Field) - True if the field is annotated with IncludeProperty
  • isExcludedByAnnotation(Method) - True if the method is annotated with ExcludeProperty
  • isExcludedByAnnotation(Field) - True if the field is annotated with ExcludeProperty
